<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Across the Indo-Pacific including Mozambique, Mauritius, the Philippines, Indonesia, Papua New Guinea, Vanuatu (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz028" author="Golestani, H" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="279 - 330" refId="B84" refString="Golestani, H, Crocetta, F, Padula, V, Camacho-Garcia, Y, Langeneck, J, Poursanidis, D, Pola, M, Yokes, MB, Cervera, JL, Jung, D-W, Gosliner, T, Araya, J-F, Hooker, Y, Schroedl, M, Valdes, A, 2019. The little Aplysia coming of age: from one species to a complex of species complexes in Aplysia parvula (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Heterobranchia). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 187: 279 - 330, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz028" title="The little Aplysia coming of age: from one species to a complex of species complexes in Aplysia parvula (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Heterobranchia)." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz028" volume="187" year="2019">Golestani et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), Maldives (
<bibRefCitation author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Saudi Arabia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B282" refString="Yonow, N, 1994. Opisthobranchs from the Maldive Islands, including descriptions of seven new species (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Revue francaise d'aquariologie (1993) 20: 97-129." title="Opisthobranchs from the Maldive Islands, including descriptions of seven new species (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Revue francaise d'aquariologie (1993) 20: 97 - 129." year="1994">Yonow 1994</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Aplysiidae" genus="Aplysia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aplysia fasciata" order="Aplysiida" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Aplysia fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the Red Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Saudi Arabia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="286 - 299" refId="B281" refString="Yonow, N, 1990. Red Sea Opisthobranchia. The orders Sacoglossa, Cephalaspidea, and Nudibranchia: Doridacea (Mollusca, Opisthobranchia). Fauna of Saudi Arabia 11: 286 - 299" title="Red Sea Opisthobranchia. The orders Sacoglossa, Cephalaspidea, and Nudibranchia: Doridacea (Mollusca, Opisthobranchia)." volume="11" year="1990">Yonow 1990</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Aplysiidae" genus="Aplysia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aplysia parvula" order="Aplysiida" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="parvula">Aplysia cf. parvula</taxonomicName>
.). Here documented as a first record for Thai waters.
</paragraph>
